  "title": "APP_ROOT_SCOPE",
  "contents": "\n\n<article>\n  <div class=\"page-actions\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/edit/master/packages/core/src/di/scope.ts?message=docs(core)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L27-L27\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/6.0.0-beta.7/packages/core/src/di/scope.ts#L27-L27\" aria-label=\"View Source\" title=\"View Source\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">code</i></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\",\n        \"itemListElement\": [\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io//api\", \"name\": \"API\" } },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core\", \"name\": \"@angular/core\" } },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core/APP_ROOT_SCOPE\", \"name\": \"APP_ROOT_SCOPE\" } }\n        ]\n      }\n    </script>\n      <a href=\"/api\">API</a> / <a href=\"api/core\">@angular/core</a>\n  </div>\n  <header class=\"api-header\">\n    <h1 id=\"app_root_scope\">APP_ROOT_SCOPE<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/APP_ROOT_SCOPE#app_root_scope\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n    <label class=\"api-type-label const\">const</label>\n    \n    <label class=\"api-status-label experimental\">experimental</label>\n    \n  </header>\n  <aio-toc class=\"embedded\"></aio-toc>\n\n  <div class=\"api-body\">\n    \n  <p class=\"short-description\"></p><p>A scope which targets the root injector.</p>\n<p></p>\n  \n  \n  \n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">\n  const <a href=\"api/core/APP_ROOT_SCOPE\" class=\"code-anchor\">APP_ROOT_SCOPE</a>: any;\n  </code-example>\n\n  \n\n  \n  \n<section class=\"description\">\n  <h2 id=\"description\">Description<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/APP_ROOT_SCOPE#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p>When specified as the <code>scope</code> parameter to <code>@<a href=\"api/core/Injectable\" class=\"code-anchor\">Injectable</a></code> or <code><a href=\"api/core/InjectionToken\" class=\"code-anchor\">InjectionToken</a></code>, this special\nscope indicates the provider for the service or token being configured belongs in the root\ninjector. This is loosely equivalent to the convention of having a <code>forRoot()</code> static\nfunction within a module that configures the provider, and expecting users to only import that\nmodule via its <code>forRoot()</code> function in the root injector.</p>\n\n</section>\n\n\n  \n\n\n  </div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/core\n - api/platform-browser/BrowserModule\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/core\n - api/core/APP_ROOT_SCOPE#app_root_scope\n - api/core/APP_ROOT_SCOPE#description\n - api/core/Injectable\n - api/core/InjectionToken\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/edit/master/packages/core/src/di/scope.ts?message=docs(core)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L27-L27\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/6.0.0-beta.7/packages/core/src/di/scope.ts#L27-L27\n-->"
